{
  "doc_id": "36737",
  "text": "The type, volume and viscosity of the monomer have been found to affect the degree of cure and thus, mechanical properties. In the literature, increasing the diluent EG-DMA and TEGDMA was found to increase the degree of cure [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] while an increase in the content of Bis-GMA resulted in a decrease in the degree of cure [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Using UDMA in a RBC showed a higher degree of cure when compared to Bis-GMA [CITATION_6] . It is therefore necessary to make a careful balance of monomer to achieve optimum properties.",
